  "riddle": "1. Seek the grand structure where cultures converge, built in the month when summer whispers began uniting traditions and creativity — which month and year graced its foundation?\n\n2. A great thoroughfare in the heart of the capital, it runs through the city with how many distinct segments, connecting stories of the past to vibrant present?\n\n3. If you ponder how far 2 of our earth's meters stretch into the vastness of the imperial system, how many feet would they become?\n\n4. Reflecting on the number harvested in the previous clue, can you find the total of its unique prime factors?\n\n5. A landmark known for its hospitality, this establishment claims how many meters in distance from the railway hub of the city?\n\n6. To ascend to new heights, discover the elevation in meters that crowns this esteemed hotel.\n\n7. Travelers describe their experiences here through ratings — what score do visitors bestow upon this cherished location?\n\n8. Combine the height you've unearthed with the appreciation of travelers, then find the absolute difference in this formula: abs(elevation from clue 6 - rating from clue 7).\n\n9. What transformation occurs when you take a mere meter and translate it into yards — how many of those yards will 1 meter yield?\n\n10. Venture forth to a region known for its local governance — what height do the lands of this district rise to?\n\n11. In reference to the height from clue 10, what is the sum of its distinct prime factors upon reflection?\n\n12. To conclude this journey, combine your discoveries from clues 2, 4, and 5, and then compute (total from clue 2 + total from clue 4 + total from clue 5) % 10. What single digit emerges from this adventure?",
